# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Environment variables. Copy to .env.local for local development.
# All .env* files are gitignored.
#
# DATABASE STRATEGY (dev/prod split):
#   • Local dev  → a disposable local SQLite file. db:migrate and db:seed
#                  run against THIS. Wiping/reseeding it is safe.
#   • Production → a remote Turso (libsql) database, configured in the Vercel
#                  project settings. Its creds also live in .env.production.local
#                  on your machine, used ONLY by `pnpm db:migrate:prod`.
#
#   Never run `pnpm db:seed` against the Turso DB — it deletes all content.
#   (The seed script refuses remote URLs unless ALLOW_REMOTE_SEED=1.)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- .env.local (local development) ---
# Local SQLite file. No auth token needed for a file: URL.
DATABASE_URL=file:./local.db

# Anthropic API key for AI features (flashcard/question generation, tutor)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# HMAC signing key for auth cookies (Mullvad-style account codes).
# Generate one: openssl rand -hex 32
AUTH_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-secret

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# --- .env.production.local (local file, gitignored) — Turso prod creds ---
# Used only by `pnpm db:migrate:prod`. Do NOT seed prod.
#
#   DATABASE_URL=libsql://<your-db>.turso.io
#   DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN=<turso-token>
#
# --- Vercel production env (set in the Vercel dashboard) ---
#   DATABASE_URL, DATABASE_AUTH_TOKEN  → the Turso database
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
#   AUTH_SECRET                        → same value across deployments or logins break
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
